      <hedline>
        <hl1>BROADCOM PICKS UP TEXAS CHIP MAKER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Broadcom Corp acquires Allayer Communications, chip maker for computer networks, for $273.5 million in stock (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The manufacturer of semiconductors for cable modems, Broadcom, said it had agreed to acquire Allayer Communications, a chip maker for computer networks, for $273.5 million in stock. The deal is part of Broadband's strategy to bolster its broadband product offering for networking services for local, metropolitan and wide area networks.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
